card-sc-ace-cups-desc = A chalice atop a pool, surrounded by flowing water. A grand bird hovers above the chalice. Water, New Feelings, Spirituality, Intuition
card-sc-two-cups-desc = Two cups, each with a snake rising from it. They intertwine and wrap around each other. Water, Unity, Partnership, Connection
card-sc-three-cups-desc = Three smiling women, each holding a cup. One is in front, holding hers above her head. The other two hold theirs above the first. Water, Friendship, Community, Happiness
card-sc-four-cups-desc = An individual presenting a cup, standing upon a table. Light shines upon it. Three cups stand at their feet. They look unhappy. Water, Apathy, Contemplation, Disconnection
card-sc-five-cups-desc = A close-up of a crying individual. Two cups stand upright behind them, three others lie scattered beneath. Water, Loss, Grief, Disappointment, Mourning
card-sc-six-cups-desc = Two rabbits flanking a tall flower. Six cups surround them, flowers sprouting from each. Water, Familiarity, Memories, Healing, Restoration
card-sc-seven-cups-desc = Seven cups upon a cloud, each containing something different. A flower, a tower, a snake, a crown, a skull, sparkles, and a mask. Water, Searching for Purpose, Choices, Daydreaming
card-sc-eight-cups-desc = A long-robed individual stepping past eight cups, stacked upon each other. A forest lies in the distance behind them. Water, Walking Away, Disillusionment, Leaving Something Behind
card-sc-nine-cups-desc = An individual seated upon a large sofa. Nine cups stand shelved above them. Water, Satisfaction, Luxury, Emotional Stability
card-sc-ten-cups-desc = Cups stacked upon each other, counting ten, with a fish leaping from the top-most. The sun shines above them, a rainbow spread before it. Water, Inner Happiness, Fulfillment, Dreams Coming True
card-sc-page-cups-desc = The Page stands holding their cup out, other hand on their hip. A fish curls out from the cup. Water, Happy Surprise, Dreamer, Sensitivity
card-sc-knight-cups-desc = The Knight rides horseback before a river of water. They hold their cup with both hands. Water, Idealistic, Romantic, Following One's Heart
card-sc-queen-cups-desc = The Queen, depicted with the lower half of a fish, holds her cup low in front of her. Seashells and algae surround her. Water, Compassion, Calm, Comfort
card-sc-king-cups-desc = The King, depicted with the lower half of a fish, holds his cup aloft. A sailboat sits on the water in the distance. Water, Emotional Control, Balance Between Heart and Head

card-sc-ace-pentacles-desc = A single, grand pentacle surrounded by vines and flowers. Earth, Opportunity, Prosperity, New Venture
card-sc-two-pentacles-desc = Two hands, each holding a pentacle. Vines spread between the two, ending in flowers. Earth, Balancing Decisions, Priorities, Adaptation
card-sc-three-pentacles-desc = Three individuals stand together; one robed, one aproned, one armored. A pentacle for each shines above them. Earth, Teamwork, Collaboration, Building Together
card-sc-four-pentacles-desc = A suited individual stands atop a pentacle, balances one on their head, and holds two more in each hand. They stand before a columned building. Earth, Conservation, Security, Frugality
card-sc-five-pentacles-desc = Cupped hands are outstretched towards a closed door. The frame is adorned with pentacles counting five. Earth, Need, Poverty, Insecurity, Low Resources
card-sc-six-pentacles-desc = Cupped hands drop six pentacles down towards two open hands. A scale rests between the two open hands. Earth, Charity, Generosity, Sharing
card-sc-seven-pentacles-desc = Crops upon farmland sprout flowering pentacles counting seven. Earth, Hard Work, Perseverance, Diligence
card-sc-eight-pentacles-desc = A smith's hammer shines brightly above an anvil, surrounded by eight pentacles. Earth, Diligence, Passion, High Standards
card-sc-nine-pentacles-desc = A closed gate adorned with pentacles lies before a lush woodland. Four pentacles on each gate door, one atop the frame. Earth, Fruits of Labor, Reckless Spending, Rewards
card-sc-ten-pentacles-desc = A large tree stands before an arch with six pentacles growing from its branches. Four more rest above it. Earth, Legacy, Inheritance, Culmination
card-sc-page-pentacles-desc = The Page stands with a pentacle in one hand, the other behind their back. Plants sprout around them. Earth, Ambition, Desire, Diligence, Craving New Adventure
card-sc-knight-pentacles-desc = The Knight rides on horseback, pentacle in hand. They stand before farmland containing tall crops. Earth, Efficiency, Hard Work, Responsibility
card-sc-queen-pentacles-desc = The Queen stands, pentacle in hand, within thick vegetation. Vines grow around her, sprouts are at her feet. Earth, Practicality, Creature Comforts, Security
card-sc-king-pentacles-desc = The King, antlers upon his head, sits upon a modest bench, pentacle upon his lap. A grand castle and forest to match lie behind him. Earth, Abundance, Prosperity, Provider, Generosity

card-sc-ace-swords-desc = A single, grand sword stands upright. A snake coils around it. A crown sits upon it, just before its end. It parts clouds, light shining past it. Air, Breakthrough, Clarity, Sharp Mind
card-sc-two-swords-desc = A blindfolded individual sits alone during a clear night. They hold two swords, their hilts crossing. Air, Difficult Choices, Indecision, Stalemate
card-sc-three-swords-desc = A heart with a crying eye, three swords piercing downward into it. Storm clouds rain upon it. Air, Heartbreak, Suffering, Grief
card-sc-four-swords-desc = A tired-looking individual stands behind a shield. Blades adorn the wall behind them, counting four. Air, Rest, Restoration, Contemplation
card-sc-five-swords-desc = Four swords raised horizontally, each crossed by one upright with a skull atop it. Gravestones lie beneath the blades. Air, Unbridled Ambition, Win At All Costs, Sneakiness
card-sc-six-swords-desc = Six blades stand upright, their hilts pointing upward, aboard a boat. The vessel moves across the waves. Air, Transition, Leaving Behind, Moving On
card-sc-seven-swords-desc = Six blades stand upright, pointed downward, in a starry night. A fox rests its paw upon the seventh, the blade pointed diagonally. Air, Deception, Trickery, Tactics and Strategy
card-sc-eight-swords-desc = An individual stands blindfolded and bound. Six blades flank them, three on each side. Two more cross in front of them. They are bleeding, blood pooling at their feet. Air, Imprisonment, Entrapment, Self-Victimization
card-sc-nine-swords-desc = A crying individual stands with their arms outstretched. Seven blades point downward toward them, two more threaten to pierce each arm. Air, Anxiety, Hopelessness, Trauma
card-sc-ten-swords-desc = An individual stands bisected, blood pooling at their feet. Ten blades cross and pierce through their body. Air, Failure, Collapse, Defeat, Backstabbing
card-sc-page-swords-desc = The Page stands atop a rock. They hold their sword by hilt and blade, resting it behind their back. Air, Curiosity, Restlessness, Mental Energy
card-sc-knight-swords-desc = The Knight rides atop a pegasus, their blade held aloft. Birds soar skyward above them. A shield is emblazoned upon their tabard. Air, Action, Impulsiveness, Defending Beliefs
card-sc-queen-swords-desc = The Queen stands with her sword held perfectly upright, her other hand behind her back. Air, Complexity, Perceptive, Clear Mindedness
card-sc-king-swords-desc = The King sits upon his throne, full armored. His sword is held upright in one hand, a globe held in the other. Air, Head Over Heart, Truth, Discipline

card-sc-ace-wands-desc = A single wand, its end alight with flame, stands tall above greenery. Fire, Creation, Willpower, Inspiration, Desire
card-sc-two-wands-desc = An individual, holding two wands, stands before a crystal ball. Cloudy mountaintops loom far behind them. Fire, Planning, Making Decisions, Leaving Home
card-sc-three-wands-desc = An individual wearing a ceremonial military suit. There is a banner emblazoned with three wands behind them. There are castle battlements further behind. Fire, Looking Ahead, Expansion, Rapid Growth
card-sc-four-wands-desc = A castle standing tall. The path leading up to it is flanked by four wands, two on each side. Fire, Community, Home, Celebration
card-sc-five-wands-desc = One wand, flanked by shields is raised skyward. Four wands cross above it. Fire, Competition, Conflict, Reality
card-sc-six-wands-desc = A knight returning home from a tour. They wield one wand, five others are banners above them. Fire, Victory, Success, Public Reward
card-sc-seven-wands-desc = A shield with two wands crossed behind it. Five wands, depicted as spears, point towards the shield. Fire, Perseverance, Mounting a Defense, Maintaining Control
card-sc-eight-wands-desc = Eight wands, depicted as arrows, shoot skyward. Birds fly alongside them, up towards the sun. Fire, Rapid Action, Movement, Quick Decisions
card-sc-nine-wands-desc = An individual stands on a battlement, holding a wand as a staff. Eight wands stand upright before the wall. Fire, Resilience, Grit, Taking Last Stand
card-sc-ten-wands-desc = A scarab holds an eye above it. Ten wands cross above it. Fire, Accomplishment, Responsibility, Burden
card-sc-page-wands-desc = The Page stands humbly, their wand as a walking staff held beside them. Mountains are far off in the distance. Fire, Exploration, Excitement, Freedom
card-sc-knight-wands-desc = The Knight rides on horseback, their wand alight with flame at its end. The sun shines behind them. Fire, Action, Adventure, Fearlessness
card-sc-queen-wands-desc = The Queen stands with two wands, alight with flame, flanking her. The sun shines behind her crowned head. Fire, Courage, Determination, Passion, Joy
card-sc-king-wands-desc = The King sits on his throne, a fire burns at his feet. Wands with burning ends frame his throne. Fire, Big Picture, Leader, Overcoming Challenges

card-sc-the-fool-desc = The beginning of the path to enlightenment. The Fool stands, dressed as such, juggling. Innocence, New Beginnings, Wonder, Foolishness
card-sc-the-magician-desc = The first step to enlightenment. The Magician stands behind a table, wielding a Wand. A Cup, Pentacle, and Sword lie upon the table. Willpower, Creation, Mastery, Adaptation
card-sc-the-high-priestess-desc = The second step to enlightenment. The High Priestess stands before two columns, book and crystal in hand. Inner Voice, Intuition, Divine Truth, Wisdom, Unconscious
card-sc-the-empress-desc = The third step to enlightenment. The Empress stands, adorned in royal robes, in a lush field. Beauty, Fertility, Nurturing, Luxury, Creativity
card-sc-the-emperor-desc = The fourth step to enlightenment. The Emperor sits, crowned, upon the throne, sceptre in hand. Mountaintops rise behind him. Structure, Ambition, Authority, Rationality
card-sc-the-hierophant-desc = The fifth step to enlightenment. The Hierophant, a man of the cloth, stands behind scripture. Two veiled individuals stand before him. Tradition, Legacy, Society, Organized Religion
card-sc-the-lovers-desc = The sixth step to enlightenment. The Lovers stand in a lush garden, fruit between them... and a snake above it. Choices, Union, Love, Relationship
card-sc-the-chariot-desc = The seventh step to enlightenment. A rocket ship, shooting for the stars, rocketing onwards. Self Control, Discipline, Success
card-sc-strength-desc = The eighth step to enlightenment. The trusty toolbox, dinged and slightly bloody, wielded by the greytider. Tools and materials lie within. Courage, Inner Strength, Conviction, Compassion
card-sc-the-hermit-desc = The ninth step to enlightenment. A robed figure stands at a cliffside, their lantern illuminating the area. Contemplation, Solitude, Insight, Awareness
card-sc-the-wheel-desc = The tenth step to enlightenment. The Wheel stands prominent, other card's depictions lie around it. Fate, Karma, Destiny, Fortune, Cycles
card-sc-justice-desc = The eleventh step to enlightenment. A sword, blade pointed downwards, with scales hanging off of both sides of its hilt. Truth, Fairness, Law, Clarity, Cause and Effect
card-sc-the-hanged-man-desc = The twelfth step to enlightenment. The Hanged Man hangs upside-down off of a post, tied by the ankle. There is a holy glow around his head. Sacrifice, Suspension, Release, Martyrdom
card-sc-death-desc = The thirteenth step to enlightenment. A skeleton stands before an open gate, scythes in each hand, crossed in front of them. Around the gate is lush greenery. End of Cycle, New Beginnings, Change, Metamorphosis
card-sc-temperance-desc = The fourteenth step to enlightenment. An angel stands eyes closed between two cups. Water flows before them and between the cups. Middle Path, Patience, Finding Meaning
card-sc-the-devil-desc = The fifteenth step to enlightenment. The Devil stands with his arms over the Lovers. Materialism, Playfulness, Pleasure, Addiction
card-sc-the-tower-desc = The sixteenth step to enlightenment. The Tower stands tall in a heavy storm, a pyre burning bright atop it. Upheaval, Disaster, Foundational Shift
card-sc-the-star-desc = The seventeenth step to enlightenment. A woman stands, stars above her, filling cups in a waterfall. She is knee-deep in water, cattails sprouting from it. Hope, Faith, Rejuvenation, Rebuilding, Healing
card-sc-the-moon-desc = The eighteenth step to enlightenment. The Moon looms over a body of water, towers upon wooded islands flanking it. The water holds two fish circling each other. Unconscious, Illusions, Intuition, Unclarity
card-sc-the-sun-desc = The nineteenth step to enlightenment. The Sun shines bright over a hill. A hand is outstretched towards it. Joy, Success, Celebration, Pleasure
card-sc-judgement-desc = The twentieth step to enlightenment. A herald of Death holds a trumpet over a graveyard. Hands reach from the ground. Reflection, Reckoning, Awakening
card-sc-the-world-desc = The final step to enlightenment. The Nanotrasen logo, along with each of the elements, meet the Fool at the end of their journey. Fulfillment, Harmony, Completion
